captions.text:
- Since you're all here, we
thought it would be fun to play
one of our new favorite games.

Here's how it works:
I've picked a category,

you have to pick the card
that's in your hand

I'll pick the answer
that I think is best.

If I pick your card,
you get a point,

and the person with the most
points wins...

There's absolutely no gift.
Um, all right.
Let's see what the first one is.

"I get by with a little help
from..."

And then you put them up
on there.

- Okay.
- And you can mix them up,
so I don't know whose is who.

"I get by with a little help
from..."

This is a tough one.
I'm gonna--

I'm gonna pick the
"Bill Nye the Science Guy."

It's hard to say who's who.
I was gonna guess, but...

- That's a game in itself.
- All right.

"I got 99 problems but blank
ain't one."

Already I think that's
the winner.

- No, I wish that was mine.
- Oh.

I'm gonna say--
oh, "balls" is gonna win.

- Although I really like
the tiny horse!

- Who did "a tiny horse"?
- That was mine.

- I've heard that's--
I've heard that's a good one.

"Licking things to claim them
as your own."

You won!
- Oh, good job, Lea.

- Thank you.
- Good job, good job.

- Aw, they're all good.
That was good, though.
All right, the next one is:

"What are my parents hiding
from me?"

- Oh, are you thinking placing
is what's getting you

the right answers,
is that your trick?

- No, I just wanted the...
- Proper placement?

- "What are my parents hiding
from me?"

And the winner is
"full frontal nudity."
I am back in this game!

- It's rigged.
- I am coming for you, Chord.
- That's how you play that game,

and we'll be right back,
everybody.

title: The Cast of 'Glee' Plays Cards Against Humanity
